         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1270">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName>, Lee was accepted as an <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">itinerant preacher</seg> in <date when="1758">1758</date>,
                  having assisted <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0879.xml"/>William
                     Grimshaw</persName> in his circuit for several years previously. In <date
                     when="1750-04">April 1750</date> he married <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1269.xml"/>Mary Brooke</persName>. Lee remained
                  steadfast in the Wesleyan work from this point until his death. See Atmore, <hi
                     rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 240–42; and <hi rend="italic">EMP</hi>,
                  4:125–69.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
